Gaming reform alliance seeks to have poker machines declared a breach of consumer law

Updated

A landmark court case that will seek to have poker machines declared in breach of consumer law could be just weeks away.

Key points: Group says poker machines are made to be addictive and deceptive

The poker machine industry rejects argument, and says it is heavily scrutinised

An advertising campaign is being launched to encourage public support

The ABC has been told the case targeting a manufacturer could start as early as next month.

A leading national law firm
